# Implementation Plan - Personal Website

## Goal
Create a high-quality, premium-feel personal website for a developer to showcase work, blogs, notes, and experience to recruiters.

## Technology Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14+ (App Router)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS + CSS Modules (for specific animations)
- **Animations**: Framer Motion
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Content**: Markdown/MDX (using `next-mdx-remote` or `react-markdown` + `gray-matter`)
- **Fonts**: Inter / Outfit (Google Fonts)

## Architecture

### Directory Structure
```
/app
  /page.tsx          (Hero, About snippet, Featured)
  /about/page.tsx    (Detailed About, Experience, Resume)
  /projects
    /page.tsx        (List of projects)
    /[slug]/page.tsx (Project documentation/details)
  /blogs
    /page.tsx
    /[slug]/page.tsx
  /notes
    /page.tsx
    /[slug]/page.tsx
/components
  /ui                (Buttons, Cards, Badges)
  /layout            (Navbar, Footer)
  /sections          (HeroSection, ExperienceSection, StackSection)
/content
  /projects          (md files)
  /blogs             (md files)
  /notes             (md files)
/lib
  /markdown.ts       (Utils to read/parse MD files)
```

